== Japanese ==
'''さん''' ([[san]]) - [[さ]] [[ん]]

=== Noun ===
A title used after person's name (first name or surname), regardless of sex.
* 山田さん - Mr/Ms Yamada. Sex is indistinguishable. 
* あきらさん - Also available for first name.
* 山田あきらさん - Mr Akira Yamada.

====Etymology====
さん is a word varied from [[様]] ([[さま]], sama). 様 is also used in more formal situation, like Sir.

====Synonyms====
*[[さま]] (様), [[ちゃん]], [[くん]] (君), [[どの]] (殿), [[どん]]

====Translation====
*English: [[Mr]], [[Ms]], [[Mrs]], [[Miss]]

